# PostgreSQL Database Configuration

# Local Development Setup
# ---------------------
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/messages_db

# Production Setup Instructions
# ---------------------------
# 1. Create a PostgreSQL database on your server
# 2. Set up a database user with appropriate permissions
# 3. Replace these values with your actual database credentials:
#    - username: Your database user
#    - password: Your database password
#    - host: Your database host (e.g., RDS endpoint)
#    - dbname: Your database name
#
# Production Example:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@host:5432/dbname
#
# Cloud Platform Examples:
# ----------------------
# Heroku: Already provides DATABASE_URL environment variable
# AWS RDS: postgresql://user:password@your-rds-endpoint:5432/dbname
# DigitalOcean: postgresql://doadmin:pass@db-postgresql-nyc3-12345:5432/defaultdb